A policy π is a function that specifies what action a to apply at a system state s. The agent receives reward rt at time step t. The value vπ(s) of a state s under a given policy π is given by the expected value of the normalized accumulated discounted rewards r with discount factor 0 ≤ γ ≤ 1 when starting in state S0 = s and following policy π:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
